# Nama, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Nama () is a rural locality (an ulus) in Kurumkansky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 93 as of 2010.
Geography
Nama is located 84&nbsp;km northeast of Kurumkan (the district's administrative centre) by road. Yagdyg is the nearest rural locality.
